column5: Superb!!!!!!
Good on ya !!!! some absolutly beautiful fish

well ive been holding off on doing a year long recap because ive been giving everything i had in me to hit a goal...  part way threw the year my brother and myself both decided that we might EACH hit 500 walleye... the bar was set and the fish more then cooperated with us...  my brother is around 600 and i just broke threw the *******1000******* mark!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!  im by no means done for the year... but now i can relax a bit... and share my year with you guys...  so my numbers as of now are  44 musky with 2 52 inchers being the biggest  1002 walleye with plenty of fish over 25 inches with the biggest being 9.6lbs local and 10.5lbs from quinte...   most of those walleye are quality size fish... but this fall i got into a jigging bite with high numbers of walleye under 18 inches... they account for about 300 fish... the other 700 were all over 18 inches... most were around 3lbs... with a 7-8lb fish gracing the net every 2 days or so...   and i even tried pike fishing this year with some success... 2 days of pike fishing got us 25 pike...   and dont think i forgot about you bass guys... even tho im not fond of them... we get some big smallies here by accident...  anyways... enough talking... heres the pics...\   hope you enjoy                                                                and walleye number 1000               what a year.......          ....
You can say that again my Friend !!!!! What a year. You did great !! I am just happy to have been a small part of that. You da man Mike  Merry Christmas to You, Maryssa and Conor !!!!
Mike , are you going fishing tomorrow ?
i might try and weasel out for a bit...   why do you ask?
Holy Muskie!
Sorry... Forgot to add these
